The Nigeria Police machine team at the weekend sur­passed all opposition’s to emerge champions at the Ist Inspector General of Police National Open Kickboxing Championship held at the Police College ground Ikeja, Lagos with seven gold, seven silver and one bronze medal while Delta State came sec­ond with six gold, and three silver. The third position went to Edo Black Scorpions club that picked five gold, seven silver and five bronze medals. The Minister of Sports, Chief Sunday Dare, com­mended the Inspector Gen­eral of Police, Alkali Baba Usman for sponsoring the championship. Represented by Mrs Nka­na Mbora, the Lagos Liason officer of the Sports Minis­try at the final, the minister thanked the IGP for collabo­rating with the Kickboxing Federation of Nigeria in putting up the championship. -Advertisement- Adding that by the act, Al­kali Baba Usman has really proven himself as a true lov­er of sports hence, he should keep it up.